   <conbody>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <hazardstatement conref="../Library/Warnings_Library_0000325173.dita#war_lib/high_current_cap-inverter"
                             platform="WxW"
                             class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
               <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
                  <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard "/>
                  <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid "/>
               </messagepanel>
            </hazardstatement>
            <hazardstatement conref="../Library/Warnings_Library_0000325173.dita#war_lib/high_current_capacitors"
                             platform="PxW"
                             class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
               <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
                  <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard "/>
                  <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid "/>
               </messagepanel>
            </hazardstatement>
            <p class="- topic/p ">If the independent system surveillance
(ISS) or independent static bypass switch (ISBS) has triggered the
unit is locked in bypass operation. Before switching to normal operation
the unit must first switch to manual bypass so that the system can
restart.</p>
            <note type="important" class="- topic/note ">Always contact <xref conref="../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/Reality_service_centers"
                     scope="local"
                     class="- topic/xref "/> if
the ISS or ISBS was triggered during operation to analyze the cause.</note>
            <p class="- topic/p ">To switch back to normal operation there are two steps:</p>
            <ol class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <xref href="#./TurnOffTheSystem-842A43A3"
                           format="dita"
                           scope="local"
                           type="section"
                           class="- topic/xref "/>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <xref href="#./RestartTheSystem-842A4554"
                           format="dita"
                           scope="local"
                           type="section"
                           class="- topic/xref "/>
                  </p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
      <section id="TurnOffTheSystem-842A43A3" class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Switch to Manual Bypass
and Turn Off the System</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">The unit needs to be turned off to allow the controller board
to reset. To turn off the system:</p>
            <ol class="- topic/ol ">
               <li otherprops="generalM 3pMBS" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <b otherprops="tempExclude" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only
for 3-position manual bypass switches:</b> Turn the manual bypass
switch to the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Test</b> position.</p>
               </li>
               <li otherprops="2pMBS" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for 2-position manual bypass switches:</b> Turn the manual bypass switch to the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass</b> position.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="PxW" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Open the battery breaker to disconnect the battery
bank.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="PxW" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Open the rectifier mains breaker to turn off
the power supply to the rectifier.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Open the inverter input switch to disconnect
the DC power supply.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Discharge the DC capacitor by keeping the charging/discharge
switch in position 1 (discharge) until the warning LED turns off.</p>
               </li>
               <li otherprops="generalM 3pMBS" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <b otherprops="tempExclude" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only
for 3-position manual bypass switches: </b>Turn the manual bypass
switch to the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass</b> position.</p>
               </li>
               <li otherprops="2pMBS" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for 2-position manual bypass switches: </b>Open the EN input switch.</p>
               </li>
            </ol>
            <p class="- topic/p ">The system is turned off and the load is supplied by the bypass.</p>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
      <section id="RestartTheSystem-842A4554" class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Restart the System</title>
         <p class="- topic/p ">After the controller board have been reset the system can be started
again, if the controller board is operable. To restart the system:</p>
         <note platform="WxW" type="important" class="- topic/note ">The DC capacitors needs to
be charged before the inverter input switch is closed.</note>
         <ol id="ISBS-restart" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the manual bypass switch is in the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass</b> position.</p>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="generalM 3pMBS" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <b otherprops="tempExclude" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only
for 3-position manual bypass switches: </b>Turn the manual bypass
switch to the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Test</b> position.</p>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="2pMBS" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for 2-position manual bypass switches: </b> Close the EN input switch.</p>
            </li>
            <li platform="PxW" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Close the rectifier mains breaker to turn on
the power supply to the rectifier.</p>
            </li>
            <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Make sure the external source of the DC input
power is available.</p>
            </li>
            <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Charge the DC capacitors:</p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Keep the charging/discharging switch it in position 2 (charge)
until the warning LED turns off.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">With the charging/discharging switch still in position 2 (charge),
close the inverter input switch. If not possible, release the charging/discharging
switch and quickly close the inverter input switch.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Release the charging/discharging switch.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">After about 10 seconds the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Standby</codeph>.</p>
               <note conref="../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/autostart_start-up"
                     class="- topic/note "/>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Lamp test button</b> and check that all operating
status and alarm LEDâ€™s are illuminated.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ON button</b> for one second on the front panel.
After a few seconds the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> will show <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Normal operation
load power ...%</codeph>.</p>
            </li>
            <li platform="PxW" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 8 key</b> to check the DC
voltage.</p>
            </li>
            <li platform="PxW" class="- topic/li ">If the DC voltage is within tolerance, close the
battery breaker.</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 9 key</b> to check that the system output
voltage is within the tolerance range.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Switch to bypass operation:</p>
               <note class="- topic/note ">The bypass mains needs
to be available and within tolerance. The static switch EN needs to
be available.</note>
               <ol conref="../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/Switch-to-bypass"
                   class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li "/>
               </ol>
               <note type="important" class="- topic/note ">Never turn the manual bypass switch from <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Test</b> to <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Auto</b> if the static switch EN is not active.</note>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Turn the manual bypass switch to the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Auto</b> position.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Switch to normal operation:</p>
               <ol conref="../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/Switch-to-normal"
                   class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li "/>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Confirm any alarms by pressing the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">C key</b> twice.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Make sure the system operates correctly and no alarms are present.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
         <p class="- topic/p ">The system is in normal operation and the load is supplied
by the system.</p>
      </section>
